This product includes software developed at LocalSky
(https://github.com/silenthooligan/localsky).

Portions of the irrigation engine are informed by:

  * FAO Irrigation and Drainage Paper No. 56 (Allen et al., 1998).
    Crop evapotranspiration: Guidelines for computing crop water
    requirements. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.

  * ASCE-EWRI Standardized Reference Evapotranspiration Equation (2005).
    American Society of Civil Engineers.

  * UF/IFAS Extension publications on Florida turfgrass species, including
    ENH6 (Bahia), ENH8 (Centipede), ENH11 (Zoysia), ENH19 (Bermuda),
    ENH62 (St. Augustine), and ENH1115 (ornamental plant irrigation).
    University of Florida Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences.

  * USDA NRCS Part 652 (National Irrigation Guide), soil infiltration and
    available-water tables.

  * The Home Assistant Smart Irrigation integration
    (https://github.com/jeroenterheerdt/HAsmartirrigation) and the
    Irrigation Unlimited integration
    (https://github.com/rgc99/irrigation_unlimited), both of which served
    as prior art for the LocalSky native engine.

This product uses (but does not redistribute the source of):

  * Open-Meteo (https://open-meteo.com/) for forecast data.
  * RainViewer (https://www.rainviewer.com/api.html) for radar tiles.
  * Leaflet (https://leafletjs.com/) for map rendering.
